        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 10:30PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1030 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Iona, or 14 miles south of Chamberlain, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Iona and Lake Francis Case.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
